posts.name: BeShock Ramen and Sake Bar
posts.note: BeShock Ramen and Sake Bar's light yet flavorful meals are quickly becoming a neighborhood hit. The broth is made from scratch and full of delicious vegetables - perfect for those looking to stay on the healthier side of dining out. Ramen, sushi roll, and even fried chicken--we have just what you need to satisfy any craving.

posts.name: El Puesto
posts.note: El Puesto is a bi-level eatery with floor-to-ceiling windows serving an innovative, locally sourced Mexican menu. They serve great upscale tacos of which I usually get the fish tacos. Haven't had a bad meal there yet.

posts.name: Fat Sal's
posts.note: Fat Sal's is a counter-serve chain featuring creative heroes, wraps burgers, hot dogs, and sides in a hip space. The sandwich to get is the Fat Sal sandwich from the guy next to me on the plane back to San Diego.

posts.name: Georges at the Cove
posts.note: Georges at the Cove is renowned chef Trey Foshee's seafood-centric cuisine served in an elegant setting with ocean views.

posts.name: Gold Donut
posts.note: The Gold Donut bakery specializes in classic glazed and filled donuts and is situated in a small shopping plaza. They make one of my top five favorite apple fritters in the country, but any of their donuts will work depending on what you're in the mood to eat.
posts.cptn: Dispaly case filled with a dozen different types of hand made donuts from Gold Donuts near Kensington area of San Diego.

posts.name: Hodad's
posts.note: At this burger joint patrons can dine inside restored cars or amid license plate-covered walls. They make one of the best burgers I have ever had which was the 'Blue Jay Burger' a bacon cheeseburger served with their blue cheese and grilled onions along a side of onion rings

posts.name: Karl Strauss Brewery
posts.note: Karl Strauss Brewery is San Diego's first microbrewery, known for its full-flavored, hand-crafted beer and six brewery restaurants. Their bar food menu is great. You should try their pork chop dish which was huge last time I had one.

posts.name: Las Cuatro Milpas
posts.note: Las Cuatro Milpas is an old-school Mexican joint earning fans with its homemade tortillas and picnic-table decor since 1933. Pork tamales with rice and beans are the dish to get and the one every other pork tamale is compared.
posts.cptn: Rice and beans with the best pork tamale I've ever eaten at Las Cuatro Milpas in San Diego, CA

posts.name: Lion's Share
posts.note: Lion's Share is an intimate, moody bar pairing handcrafted drinks with New American plates featuring exotic meats. I have ordered many things here from a mixed sausage platter to pork chop to some Charcuterie, and it's all been great.

posts.name: Lucha Libre Taco Shop
posts.note: Lucha Libre Taco Shop serves authentic street-style Mexican dishes, plus a salsa bar and old wrestling matches on TV. NOTE I was waiting at a light to turn on the highway at 12:30 PM and there was a line out the door so figured it might need to be on the list.

posts.name: OB Noodle House and Sake Bar
posts.note: Bustling restaurant and bar specializes in pho, beer on tap, and a wide variety of sake drinks. Saw this place as we drove by heading to Hodad's and there was a line out the door and fiured I needed to add it to the list for later.

posts.name: Phil's BBQ
posts.note: Casual eatery and bar for signature mesquite-barbecued baby-back & beef ribs, plus sandwiches and sides.

posts.name: Richard Walker's Pancake House
posts.note: Diners line up for baked apple pancakes and hearty breakfast staples at this casual daytime eatery.

posts.name: Soda and Swine
posts.note: Hip eatery with an open roof offering meatballs, soft-serve ice cream and a large selection of sodas. Make sure to get the Scotch egg and a variety of meatball sliders. Their classic beef and pork are tender and juicy.
posts.cptn: Metal tray with our sliders from Soda and Swine in San Diego which are Banh-mi, beef meatball, chorizo, and pork.

posts.name: Tajima Ramen Bar
posts.note: Ramen restaurant with an industrial-chic design has several toppings to choose from and rice bowls. If you can muster up two more friends it's well worth your effeort to order all four types of Ramen for the three of you can share. That is if your friends don't mind sharing Ramen.
